ce:section.ce:para:
Under the optimal detecting conditions, the fluorescence spectra of AuNCs@11-MUA/Cu2+ at different concentrations of GSH were determined. As shown in Fig. 3
                        (a), the fluorescence intensity of AuNCs at 595 nm gradually increases when the GSH concentration is in the range of 0–12 μM. At lower concentration of GSH, the degree of fluorescence enhancement is greater. When the concentration of GSH was higher than 6 μM, the fluorescence enhancement trend is greatly reduced. Fig. 3(b) shows that the fluorescence recovery rate of the system has a good linear relationship with the concentration of GSH in the range of 0.05–5 μM, and the detection limit is 33.3 nM (S/N = 3). Compared with other fluorescent nanoprobes reported in the literatures (Table 1
                        ), the proposed probe exhibits distinguished sensitivity.
